	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St Louis</placeName> <date>April 16&#47;54</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">I shall remit to<lb/> you by the end of this week my reasons<lb/> for writing now is that I have spare time<lb/> <sic>wheras</sic> in the week my time is so taken<lb/> up by labor that I avail myself of the<lb/> present time&#44; the following persons<lb/> in your list are not in the city <persName>S. Keller</persName><lb/> <persName>J H Cohen</persName>&#44; <persName>A N Hart</persName> &#38; <persName>W St Johns</persName> of those<lb/> here the following refused to take the bible<lb/> <persName>M. Abrahams</persName>. <persName>J Barnum</persName> <persName>A Langsdorf</persName> <persName>J Woolf</persName><lb/> <persName>A L Kumell</persName>. <persName>L H Plahto</persName> <persName>J Micathened</persName><lb/> to have them advertised in the Occident<lb/> particularly as <persName>H Plahto</persName> gave me an order<lb/> for a set of <persName>Piza</persName> Books according to your<lb/> circular.  I Received from <persName>Mr Lats</persName> their<lb/> Tiphillas<add>&#63;</add> 1&#45;250&#45;1&#45;2.75 &#38; 1&#44;5.000 The 2.75 one<lb/> I sold at &#36;3.00 I also sold the 2.50 one the other is<lb/> much <sic>soild</sic> and will never bring the price you<lb/> will please inform me <sic>wether</sic> I shall return<lb/> it to <persName>Mr Lats</persName> a sett is for 3.00 as I think<lb/> that is about as much as it will bring<lb/> it may fetch 50&#47;cents more.  I received <persName>Dias</persName> Letters<lb/> through the mail also the four Hagodahs which<lb/> came very opportune I shall now give you</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>of my stewardship I sold to private persons<lb/> four copies of the bible 2 a 11.00 &#38; 2&#8212;8.00<lb/> besides several <persName>Dias</persName> Letters I had also to<lb/> pay one Sharnas five pr cent on<lb/> one hundred and five dollars the persons being<lb/> at a distance than in my neighborhood<lb/> I collect myself a shall do it</p>
				<table rows="11" cols="4">
				<row>
				<cell><persName role="author">H Myers</persName> Dr to <persName>I Leeser</persName></cell>
				<cell/>
				<cell><persName role="author">H Myers</persName> Or</cell>
				<cell/>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell>To <sic>ballance</sic> of Bill&#8212;</cell>
				<cell>50</cell>
				<cell>Freight &#38;c</cell>
				<cell>10.50</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell>1 Bible <add>&#63;</add></cell>
				<cell>9&#8212;</cell>
				<cell>5 pr cent 105</cell>
				<cell>5.25</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell>1 Set <persName>Piza</persName> Books</cell>
				<cell>25&#8212;</cell>
				<cell/>
				<cell>&#36;15.75</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell>13 Bibles 8&#8212;</cell>
				<cell>104&#8212;</cell>
				<cell/>
				<cell>165.25</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell>1&#8212;</cell>
				<cell>9&#8212;</cell>
				<cell/>
				<cell/>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell>8 <persName>Dias</persName> <add>&#63;</add></cell>
				<cell>6&#8212;</cell>
				<cell/>
				<cell/>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell>1 Tephillim</cell>
				<cell>2 50</cell>
				<cell/>
				<cell/>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell/>
				<cell>3&#8212;</cell>
				<cell/>
				<cell/>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell/>
				<cell>159&#8212;</cell>
				<cell/>
				<cell/>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell>2 Bibles 11&#45;00</cell>
				<cell>18.100.</cell>
				<cell/>
				<cell/>
				</row>
				</table>
				<p>from this &#36;165.25 will be deducted Exchange &#38;<lb/> discount&#44; you will please charge<lb/> a <persName>J Lats</persName> with 1 <persName>Dias</persName> letters you<lb/> will also send the occident to <persName>J. A Hart</persName><lb/> of this city commencing if come with the<lb/> first number just out he his good <add>&#63;</add><lb/> I have now on hand 5 Bibles at &#36;800<lb/> 1 at &#36;9.00 2 at &#36;11.00 &#38; 6 <persName>Dias</persName> Letter&#39;s<lb/> you may rely upon my using my<lb/> <sic>axertions</sic> to affect sales it <sic>ocurrs</sic> to me</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>that it would be a good plan to advertise<lb/> them but the <sic>expence</sic> would not <add>&#63;</add><lb/> me in doing so without your consent<lb/> the following Name I got to your<lb/> prayer Books according to the<lb/> German &#38; Polish Jews</p>
				<table rows="4" cols="4">
				<row>
				<cell><persName>R Kiche</persName></cell>
				<cell>2 copies</cell>
				<cell><persName>L M Prima</persName></cell>
				<cell>1 copy</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell><persName>A S Myers</persName></cell>
				<cell>1&#8220;</cell>
				<cell><persName>J A Hart</persName></cell>
				<cell>1&#8220;</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell><persName>A Newark</persName></cell>
				<cell>2&#8220;</cell>
				<cell><persName>H Plahto</persName></cell>
				<cell>1&#8220;</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell><persName>J Kohn</persName></cell>
				<cell>1&#8220;</cell>
				<cell><persName role="author">H S Myers</persName></cell>
				<cell>1&#8220;</cell>
				</row>
				</table>
			<p rend="indent(1)">10 copies in all</p>
				<p>let me know in your next if<lb/> you have commenced then the above<lb/> named persons are all of this city<lb/> I have <add>&#63;</add> your circular<lb/> with my best wishes for your<lb/> welfare I subscribe</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">Myself yours Respectfully<add>&#63;</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">H Myers</persName></p>
				<p><placeName>Box 1515</placeName></p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Editor Occident</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
